  "id": "019d2d76-2d2a-73e2-9b53-1f6bb6fbee14",
  "content": "## Dev Loop Skill — Formalized Development Process (2026-03-27)\n\n### Decision\nCreated the `dev-loop` skill (`.agents/skills/dev-loop/`) as the mandatory development workflow for all GitHub issue work. This formalizes the full autonomous development lifecycle.\n\n### Pipeline Phases\n1. **Issue Intake** — `gh issue view` + `corvia_search`/`corvia_ask` for context + feature branch creation\n2. **Brainstorm & Design** — `superpowers:brainstorming` (hard gate: design must be approved)\n3. **Implementation Plan** — `superpowers:writing-plans`\n4. **Implementation** — `superpowers:subagent-driven-development` (task-by-task with per-task reviews)\n5. **5-Persona Review** — 3 standard (Senior SWE, PM, QA) + 2 dynamic (task-dependent). Each reviewer is an independent deep subagent run with 10+ lines of substantive feedback. Fix-review loop until all Critical/Important/Low issues resolved (max 3 iterations).\n6. **E2E Integration Testing** — Happy path, edge cases, integration points, regression, full test suite\n7. **Branch, PR, Merge** — Push, PR with review summary, merge with conflict resolution, cleanup, corvia_write\n\n### Review Upgrade\nUpgraded from 3-persona to 5-persona review. Dynamic reviewer selection table covers: Performance, Security, API, UI, Infrastructure, Data/ML, Rust-specific, and General categories.\n\n### Invocation\n`/dev-loop <issue-number>` slash command in Claude Code.\n\n### Files Created\n- `.agents/skills/dev-loop/SKILL.md` — Main skill definition\n- `.agents/skills/dev-loop/five-persona-reviewer.md` — Review prompt template\n- `.agents/skills/dev-loop/e2e-tester.md` — E2E test prompt template\n- `.claude/commands/dev-loop.md` — Slash command definition",
